SIMPLE: denunciation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Denunciation
<hw>De*nun`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>denuntiatio</ets>, <ets>-ciatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Proclamation; announcement; a publishing.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Public . . . <qex>denunciation</qex> of banns before marriage.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of denouncing; public menace or accusation;
the act of inveighing against, stigmatizing, or publicly arraigning;
arraignment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That by which anything is denounced; threat of evil;
public menace or accusation; arraignment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Uttering bold <qex>denunciations</qex> of ecclesiastical
error.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Denunciative</ent>⟦br⟧
